HEADWORD: Desquamate
<hw>Des"qua*mate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>desquamatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>desquamare</ets> to scale off;
<ets>de-</ets> + <ets>squama</ets> scale.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>To peel off in the form of scales; to scale off, as the skin in
certain diseases.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Desquamation</ent>⟦br⟧
